    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-11-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="989"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d989">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Peirce</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Hay approves the protocol transmitted with Mr. Peirce’s No. 139, except that
                    the “<hi rend="italic">Cape Horn Pigeon</hi>” should be described as having been
                    engaged in whaling instead of sealing.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
